        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-xl p-6 m-4 max-w-lg w-full relative">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0077B6] mb-4">The IRS "Below-Market Interest" Rule</h3>
            <p class="text-[#03045E] mb-4">Even in amicable buyouts, a 0% interest loan can cause unintended tax problems. The IRS requires private loans to have an interest rate at least equal to the <strong class="text-black">Applicable Federal Rate (AFR)</strong>.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 text-left">
                <li>If the rate is 0%, the IRS can "impute" interest, meaning Adam would have to report and pay taxes on "phantom" interest income he never actually received.</li>
                <li>The forgiven interest could also be considered a taxable gift from Adam to Jane.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-[#023E8A] font-semibold">Setting the interest rate to the AFR (e.g., 4.77%) is not about profiting from the loan; it's a necessary step for tax compliance that protects both parties from future IRS complications.</p>
            <button id="close-modal" class="absolute top-3 right-3 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800">
                 <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"></path></svg>
            </button>
        </div>
